                    <history>
                        <origin>According to the information of <locus target="#2r">f. 2r</locus>
                            and <locus target="#38r">38r</locus>, this volume was written during the reign of king
                            <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS9430Tewodros">Theodore</persName>, when <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS3500Demetriu">Demetrius</persName> was patriarch of Alexandria
                            and <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS8388SalamaI">Salāmā III</persName> ʾabuna of Ethiopia.
                            
                            <origDate evidence="reign" notBefore="1861" notAfter="1867"/>
                        </origin>
                        <provenance>The manuscript had very probably belonged to a church in the <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC3577Gondar">Gondar</placeName> area,
                            from where it was taken by
                            <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS9430Tewodros">Tewodros</persName> and brought to <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0101MadhaneAlam">Madḫāne ʿĀlam</placeName>. It was then looted
                            by the British <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS7484Napier">Napier</persName> expedition in <date>1868</date>.</provenance>
                        
                    </history>
